ArchiveKey.document: This API is used to archive keys.The archived keys can only be used for decryption but not encryption.
ArchiveKey.name: Archives keys

AsymmetricRsaDecrypt.document: This API is used to decrypt data with the specified private key that is encrypted with RSA asymmetric cryptographic algorithm. The ciphertext must be encrypted with the corresponding public key. The asymmetric key must be in `Enabled` state for decryption.
AsymmetricRsaDecrypt.name: Decrypts data with an RSA asymmetric key

AsymmetricSm2Decrypt.document: This API is used to decrypt data with the specified private key that is encrypted with SM2 asymmetric cryptographic algorithm. The ciphertext must be encrypted with the corresponding public key. The asymmetric key must be in `Enabled` state for decryption. The length of the ciphertext passed in cannot exceed 256 bytes.
AsymmetricSm2Decrypt.name: Decrypts data with an SM2 asymmetric key

BindCloudResource.document: This API is used to bind a key with a Tencent Cloud resource. If the key has been set to be expired automatically, the setting will be canceled to ensure that the key will not be invalid automatically. If the key and the resource has already been bound, the call will still be successful.
BindCloudResource.name: Binds a key with a Tencent Cloud resource

CancelDataKeyDeletion.document: This API is used to cancel scheduled deletion for a data key.
CancelDataKeyDeletion.name: Cancel scheduled deletion of a data key

CancelKeyArchive.document: This API is used to unarchive keys. If a key is unarchived, its status will be `Enabled`.
CancelKeyArchive.name: Unarchives keys

CancelKeyDeletion.document: Cancel the scheduled deletion of CMK
CancelKeyDeletion.name: Cancel CMK plan delete operation

CreateKey.document: Create a master key CMK (Custom Master Key) for user management data keys
CreateKey.name: Create master key

CreateWhiteBoxKey.document: This API is used to create a white-box key. Up to 50 ones can be created.
CreateWhiteBoxKey.name: Creates a white-box key

Decrypt.document: This API is used to decrypt the ciphertext and obtain the plaintext data.
Decrypt.name: Decrypt

DeleteImportedKeyMaterial.document: This API is used to delete the imported key material. It is only valid for EXTERNAL CMKs. Specifically, it puts a CMK into `PendingImport` status instead of deleting the CMK, so that the CMK can be used again after key material is reimported. To delete the CMK completely, please call the `ScheduleKeyDeletion` API.
DeleteImportedKeyMaterial.name: Deletes imported key material

DeleteWhiteBoxKey.document: This API is used to delete a white-box key. Note: only disabled white-box keys can be deleted.
DeleteWhiteBoxKey.name: Deletes a white-box key

DescribeDataKey.document: This API is used to retrieve data key details.
DescribeDataKey.name: Retrieve data key details

DescribeDataKeys.document: This API is used to return the key attribute information list.
DescribeDataKeys.name: Retrieve key details

DescribeKey.document: This API is used to get the attribute details of the CMK with a specified `KeyId`.
DescribeKey.name: Gets CMK attributes

DescribeKeys.document: This API is used to get the attribute information of CMKs in batches.
DescribeKeys.name: Gets attributes of multiple CMKs

DescribeWhiteBoxDecryptKey.document: This API is used to get a white-box decryption key.
DescribeWhiteBoxDecryptKey.name: Gets a white-box decryption key

DescribeWhiteBoxDeviceFingerprints.document: This API is used to get the device fingerprint list of a specified key.
DescribeWhiteBoxDeviceFingerprints.name: Gets the device fingerprint list of a specified key

DescribeWhiteBoxKey.document: This API is used to display white-box key information.
DescribeWhiteBoxKey.name: Displays white-box key information

DescribeWhiteBoxKeyDetails.document: This API is used to get the white-box key list.
DescribeWhiteBoxKeyDetails.name: Gets the white-box key list

DescribeWhiteBoxServiceStatus.document: This API is used to get the white-box key service status.
DescribeWhiteBoxServiceStatus.name: Gets the white-box key service status

DisableDataKey.document: This API is used to disable the data key.
DisableDataKey.name: Disabling a data key

DisableDataKeys.document: This API is used to batch disable data keys.
DisableDataKeys.name: Bulk disable data keys

DisableKey.document: This API is used to disable a master key. The disabled key cannot be used for encryption and decryption operations.
DisableKey.name: Disable master key

DisableKeyRotation.document: Disabled key rotation for the specified CMK.
DisableKeyRotation.name: Disable key rotation

DisableKeys.document: This API is used to batch prohibit the use of CMK.
DisableKeys.name: Disable master keys in bulk

DisableWhiteBoxKey.document: This API is used to disable a white-box key.
DisableWhiteBoxKey.name: Disables a white-box key

DisableWhiteBoxKeys.document: This API is used to disable white-box keys in batches.
DisableWhiteBoxKeys.name: Disables white-box keys in batches

EnableDataKey.document: This API is used to enable the data key.
EnableDataKey.name: Enables the data key

EnableDataKeys.document: This API is used to batch enable data keys.
EnableDataKeys.name: Batch enable data keys

EnableKeyRotation.document: Turn on the key rotation function for the specified CMK.
EnableKeyRotation.name: Turn on key rotation

EnableKeys.document: This API is used to enable CMK in batches.
EnableKeys.name: Batch start master key

EnableWhiteBoxKey.document: This API is used to enable a white-box key.
EnableWhiteBoxKey.name: Enables a white-box key

EnableWhiteBoxKeys.document: This API is used to enable white-box keys in batches.
EnableWhiteBoxKeys.name: Enables white-box keys in batches

Encrypt.document: This API is used to encrypt any data up to 4KB. It can be used to encrypt database passwords, RSA Key, or other small sensitive information. For application data encryption, use the DataKey generated by GenerateDataKey to perform local data encryption and decryption operations
Encrypt.name: encryption

EncryptByWhiteBox.document: This API is used to encrypt data with a white-box key.
EncryptByWhiteBox.name: Encrypts data with a white-box key

GenerateDataKey.document: This API generates a data key, which you can use to encrypt local data.
GenerateDataKey.name: Generate data key

GenerateRandom.document: This API is used to generate a random number.
GenerateRandom.name: Generates a random number

GetDataKeyCiphertextBlob.document: This API is used to download the encrypted data key.
GetDataKeyCiphertextBlob.name: Download the ciphertext of the data key

GetDataKeyPlaintext.document: This API is used to retrieve the key plaintext.
GetDataKeyPlaintext.name: Retrieve the plaintext of the data key

GetKeyRotationStatus.document: Query whether the specified CMK has the key rotation function.
GetKeyRotationStatus.name: Query key rotation status

GetParametersForImport.document: This API is used to obtain the parameters of the material to be imported into a CMK. The returned `Token` is used as one of the parameters to execute `ImportKeyMaterial`, and the returned `PublicKey` is used to encrypt the key material. The `Token` and `PublicKey` are valid for 24 hours. If they are expired, you will need to call the API again to get a new `Token` and `PublicKey`.
GetParametersForImport.name: Gets the parameters of the material to be imported into a CMK

GetPublicKey.document: This API is used to get the public key of an asymmetric KMS key (which must be enabled). With the public key, you can encrypt messages and verify signatures.
GetPublicKey.name: Gets the information of the public key that is encrypted with the asymmetric cryptographic algorithm

GetRegions.document: This API is used to return all regions support KMS service.
GetRegions.name: Return all regions support KMS service

GetServiceStatus.document: Used to query whether the user has activated the KMS service.
GetServiceStatus.name: Query service status

ImportDataKey.document: Data key import API, managed by KMS.
ImportDataKey.name: Import a data key

ImportKeyMaterial.document:
This API is used to import key material into an EXTERNAL CMK. The key obtained through the `GetParametersForImport` API is used to encrypt the key material. You can only reimport the same key material into the specified CMK and set a new expiration time. After the CMK key material is imported, it cannot be replaced. After the key material is expired or deleted, the CMK will remain unavailable until the same key material is reimported. CMKs are independent, which means that the same key material can be imported into different CMKs, but data encrypted by one CMK cannot be decrypted by another one.
Key material can only be imported into CMKs in `Enabled` and `PendingImport` status.
ImportKeyMaterial.name: Imports key material

ListAlgorithms.document: This API is used to list the encryption methods supported in the current region.
ListAlgorithms.name: Lists encryption methods supported in the current region

ListDataKeyDetail.document: This API is used to retrieve data key list details based on specified Offset and Limit.
ListDataKeyDetail.name: Retrieve data key list details

ListDataKeys.document: This API is used to query the list of data keys.
ListDataKeys.name: Retrieve data key list

ListKeyDetail.document: Get the master key list details according to the specified Offset and Limit.
ListKeyDetail.name: Get master key list details

ListKeys.document: This API is used to list the KeyIds of CMKs in `Enabled`, `Disabled`, and `PendingImport` status under the account.
ListKeys.name: Get master key list

OverwriteWhiteBoxDeviceFingerprints.document: This API is used to overwrite the device fingerprint information of a specified key.
OverwriteWhiteBoxDeviceFingerprints.name: Overwrites the device fingerprint information of a specified key

PostQuantumCryptoDecrypt.document: This API is used to decrypt ciphertext using post-quantum cryptography (PQC) algorithm, and return the plaintext.
PostQuantumCryptoDecrypt.name: Decrypts with PQC

PostQuantumCryptoEncrypt.document: This API is used to encrypt using PQC. It supports up to 4 KB of data. It is applicable for encryption of database passwords, RSA keys, or other sensitive information. You can also apply `DataKey` generated by API `GenerateDataKey` to encrypt or decrypt your local data.
PostQuantumCryptoEncrypt.name: Encrypts with PQC

PostQuantumCryptoSign.document: This API is used to sign using PQC.
PostQuantumCryptoSign.name: Signs with PQCDecrypts with PQC

PostQuantumCryptoVerify.document: This API is used to verify a signature using PQC.
PostQuantumCryptoVerify.name: Verifies a signature with PQC

ReEncrypt.document: Re-encrypt the ciphertext using the specified CMK.
ReEncrypt.name: Ciphertext refresh

ScheduleDataKeyDeletion.document: Schedule deletion for a data key.
ScheduleDataKeyDeletion.name: Schedule deletion of a data key

ScheduleKeyDeletion.document: CMK planned deletion API, used to specify the time of CMK deletion, the optional time interval is [7,30] days
ScheduleKeyDeletion.name: CMK plan delete API

SignByAsymmetricKey.document:
This API is used to generate a signature with an asymmetric key.
Note that only when KeyUsage is `ASYMMETRIC_SIGN_VERIFY_${ALGORITHM}` (e.g., `ASYMMETRIC_SIGN_VERIFY_SM2` and `ASYMMETRIC_SIGN_VERIFY_ECC`), the key can be used for signing.
SignByAsymmetricKey.name: Generates a signature

UnbindCloudResource.document: This API is used to unbind a key with a Tencent Cloud resource, indicating that the Tencent Cloud resource will not use the key any longer.
UnbindCloudResource.name: Unbinds a CMK with a Tencent Cloud resource

UpdateAlias.document: This API is used to modify the alias of a CMK. CMKs in `PendingDelete` status cannot be modified.
UpdateAlias.name: Modify alias

UpdateDataKeyDescription.document: This API is used to modify the description of a data key.
UpdateDataKeyDescription.name: Modify data key description

UpdateDataKeyName.document: This API is used to modify the data key name.
UpdateDataKeyName.name: Modify the data key name

UpdateKeyDescription.document: This API is used to modify the description of the specified CMK. CMKs in `PendingDelete` status cannot be modified.
UpdateKeyDescription.name: Modify master key description

VerifyByAsymmetricKey.document: This API is used to verify a signature with an asymmetric key.
VerifyByAsymmetricKey.name: Verifies a signature

Values: `SM2`(Return the ciphertext in the format of "C1C3C2"), `SM2_C1C3C2_ASN1` (Return the ciphertext in the format of "C1C3C2 ASN1"), `RSAES_PKCS1_V1_5`, `RSAES_OAEP_SHA_1`, `RSAES_OAEP_SHA_256`. It defaults to `SM2` if it's not specified.
members.name: EncryptionAlgorithm

members.document: Globally unique CMK ID
members.name: KeyId

members.document:
If `EncryptionPublicKey` is left empty, a Base64-encoded ciphertext will be returned. To get the plaintext, you need to decode the ciphertext first.
If `EncryptionPublicKey` is passed in, this field contains the Base64-encoded ciphertext after asymmetric encryption by using the public key in `EncryptionPublicKey` To get the plaintext, you need to first decode the Base64 format, and then decrypwith the private key corresponding with the public key. The private key is uploaded by the user.
